<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Donny van de Beek has told his Ajax team-mates he is signing for Manchester United, according to reports. </p>

<p>The 23-year-old midfielder has been strongly linked with a move to the Red Devils this summer, as Ole Gunnar Solskjaer plans to bolster his midfield options ahead of the 2020-21 season.</p>

<p>Tottenham and Barcelona are also believed to be keen on the Ajax star, who scored ten goals in 37 appearances for the Dutch Eredivisie side last season.</p>

<p>Ajax midfielder Donny van de Beek appears to have chosen Manchester United as his next club</p>

<p>The 23-year-old midfielder (left) has reportedly told team-mates he is joining United this year</p>

<p>But according to Spanish news outlet SPORT, van de Beek has already informed his team-mates of his next destination and will fly to Manchester next week to complete the deal.</p>

<p>The report says Ronald Koeman was keen on bringing his fellow countryman to the Camp Nou this summer but the LaLiga club baulked at the £50million asking price for the midfielder. </p>

<p>And Manchester United, who are interested in for Aston Villa midfielder Jack Grealish, have moved ahead of the Catalans in the queue for van de Beek - and their interest in resulted in him being he was left out of Ajax's friendly against Eintracht Frankfurt on Saturday.</p>

<p>Ajax boss Erik Ten Haag said: 'There are indeed developments that prevent him from being in the selection. We are looking at how that will end.'</p>

<p>United boss Ole Gunnar Solskjaer (above) wants to bolster his midfield options for next year </p>

<p>Van de Beek scored 10 goals last season and is also wanted by Barcelona and Tottenham</p>

<p>While the transfer window closes on October 5, the Dutch giants would like van de Beek's future sorted by September 13, when they begin their league season against Sparta Rotterdam. </p>

<p>The 23-year-old has been involved in Ajax's pre-season campaign so far and even played in a couple of friendlies this week. </p>

<p>The midfielder has made 175 appearances in all competitions for his boyhood club, since coming through the youth ranks in 2015.</p>

<p>He was part of the Ajax side who reached the Champions League last four in 2019 and scored in the last-16, quarter-final and semi-final rounds.  </p>
